<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Governor of Pennsylvania</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-12-22"><hi rend="italic">December 22,
                                    1897</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to your letter of 11th instant, I desire to say that the
                            Austrian minister is pressing for a copy of the promised Hazleton
                            investigation report concerning the killing and wounding of Austrian
                            subjects in September last. Please expedite, if possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>